## Universal CLI tools every strain needs, GUI or headless. No desktop
## environment here on purpose — DE choice (or none, for server/cloud) is
## a per-strain decision, see iso/strains/*.list.chroot and iso/build.sh's
## --strain handling. (Previously this file had NO desktop environment
## package anywhere, which meant the original skeleton would have produced
## a GUI-less image regardless of strain -- caught and fixed while adding
## strain selection, see TODO.md.)
curl
jq
git
build-essential
cmake
linux-tools-common
## Must match the HWE kernel build.sh installs (--linux-flavours
## generic-hwe-24.04), NOT the GA kernel. linux-tools-common ships the
## /usr/bin/cpupower|perf wrappers that exec /usr/lib/linux-tools/$(uname -r)/<tool>;
## the GA linux-tools-generic never installs the HWE-ABI directory, so cpupower
## (used by distro-modectl for every performance mode) would fail at runtime
## once the HWE ABI diverges from GA. The -hwe-24.04 tools track the HWE ABI.
linux-tools-generic-hwe-24.04
power-profiles-daemon
mokutil
ffmpeg
openssh-server
## Explicit device firmware (WiFi/GPU/Bluetooth blobs). Almost always pulled in
## transitively by the HWE kernel + ubuntu-desktop-minimal, but pinned here so a
## first flash never boots with a dead Intel iwlwifi radio just because a
## transitive Recommends got dropped. Belt-and-suspenders, no downside.
linux-firmware
